# Presentations — slide discipline

Full cheat-sheet: [`presentations/SLIDE-RULES.md`](../../presentations/SLIDE-RULES.md)

## One-slide budget

Each `##` slide: **one** primary block (≤ 4 bullets, or ≤ 3-row table, or ≤ 5-line code/ASCII) plus **≤ 2** supporting lines. No stacking blocks.

## Anti-patterns that cause overflow

- **Missing `---` between slides** — next `##` silently merges into previous slide
- **Standalone bold intro line before the list** — the `##` heading names the topic; drop the preamble
- **Preamble paragraph before primary block** — move to speaker notes
- **4+ appendix entries on one slide** — 2 per slide, use `(continued)` for more

## Split, never shrink

Move overflow to a `(continued)` slide, speaker notes `<!-- ... -->`, or the appendix. Never delete a concept to fit.

## After edits

Run `marp presentations/<deck>.md --pdf -o /tmp/check.pdf` and scroll every slide. Any clip → split.
